#If the bill was $150.00, split between 5 people, with 12% tip. 

#Each person should pay (150.00 / 5) * 1.12 = 33.6
#Format the result to 2 decimal places = 33.60

#Tip: There are 2 ways to round a number. You might have to do some Googling to solve this.ðŸ’ª

#Write your code below this line ðŸ‘‡
bill=(int(input("welcome to the tip calculator!\n what was the total bill?\n")))
tip_amount=(int(input("how much tip would you like to give? 10,12 or 15\n")))
split=(int(input("how much people to split the bill?")))
percentage=(tip_amount/100)
total_bill=bill+percentage
people=(bill/split)
print(round(people))
